The paper proposes an adaptive approach to clustering using classes of parametrized Bregman divergences, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. Specifically, the paper focuses on clustering heterogeneous data, which involves dealing with data that have different dispersion or topology among attributes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), statistics (cs.ST), and computational linguistics (cs.CL), which are all relevant to the topic of clustering and heterogeneous data.
